<p>How do i make an entire TableView not focusable?</p>  <p>When i do</p>  <pre><code>TableView.setFocusTraversable(false); </code></pre>  <p>i can still click the header and focus the TableView. When the table has been drawn and i lookup the header and also do <code>header.setFocusTraversable(false)</code> it still does not work. Maybe because <code>setFocusTraversable</code> does not work the same as <code>setFocusable</code> in Java swing, yet <code>setFocusTraversable</code> works for the entire TableView except when i click the header for the columns.</p>